I have recently discovered from my wife that this sort of recipe is actually an old Chinese (Taiwanese) royal delicacy from hundreds of years ago - pre-Kellogs, but still using some puffed crisped rice as the base with a syrupy mixture to bind them.<br />
<br />
They also flavour it with brow sugar, taro, or even green tea (yuck!)<br />
