					<hr size="1" noshade />
					<div class="commentheading">On September 01, 2006 at 07:18 PM, Michael Chu said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody"><div class='commentquote'>Anonymous wrote:<div class='commentquotebody'>...when we add the rice crispy we turn off the heat or we keep it on? thanks</div></div><br />
You can leave it on or turn it off. If you do leave it on, just keep it on low to help keep the marshmallow flowing as you mix in the rice crispies. More often than not, I turn off the heat and mix in the rice crispies before it cools enough to become difficult to mix.</div>
