					<div class="commentheading">On September 18, 2006 at 02:29 AM, Jim (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>Rice Krispy Treats</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">A couple of tips - spray pan with Pam cooking spray.  Also spray a plastic spatula with the same stuff.  It allows the mixture to slide into place when pressing it out in the pan without sticking to the pan and the spatula.<br />
Don't heat the marshmallows until they are completely melted - add the cereal just before they lose their individual shapes, and they will be dispersed among the bars.  With enough corn syrup and a little peanut butter, the cereal will still adhere enough to form bars.  Remember, marshmallows are almost pure sugar plus elasticizer.</div>
