					<div class="commentheading">On March 26, 2009 at 01:25 PM, www.ascendiac.com (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>sRKT Recipe</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">When I saw the cost of the "energy bars" my wife was eating as a snack, I decided to see if I could massage this recipe into a reasonable substitute. Call it sRKT, for superRiceKrispieTreats.<br />
<br />
INPUT:<br />
3 Tablespoons butter<br />
4 Tablespoons peanut butter<br />
1/2 cup chocolate (chips, chunks, candy bar pieces, etc.)<br />
1 cup chopped nuts. Any type will do.<br />
10 oz. marshmallows<br />
6 cups puffed rice cereal<br />
<br />
TRANSFER FUNCTION: (It's for engineers, right?!?)<br />
In a large (preferably non-stick) pot, warming on the lowest stove top heat setting, place the butter. Wait for it to melt. Add the peanut butter and mix them together (convolve). When mixed, convolve chocolate. When mixed, convolve nuts. When mixed, convolve marshmallows. When melted, convolve cereal. Put in wax paper-lined baking pan. Cool to room temperature, cut, and eat.<br />
<br />
OUTPUT:<br />
Protein-enriched, choco-peanutbutter rice treats.<br />
<br />
If you want to help out, visit my Web site and buy a copy of my  non-cooking-related novel. Yes, I have too much free time. -W<br />
<br />
http://www.ascendiac.com</div>
